frameDefinitions: While in motion, an Impactor makes sudden, forcible contact with the Impactee, or two Impactors both move, mutually making forcible contact.
A Sound emitted by a  Sound_source, which construed as a single point, moves along a Path.
An Astronomical_entity comes into view above the horizon as part of a regular, periodic process of (apparent) motion of the Astronomical_entity across the sky.
This frame is  concerned with the percepts that vibrations which travel through the air or another medium produce in hearing organs.
An Agent causes an Impactor to make sudden, forcible contact with an Impactee, or manipulates two (or more) Impactors so that they make mutual forcible contact.
This frame involves words that provide a measure for some undelimited (mass) Entity by referring to an Event that a prototypical quantity (or duration) of the Entity stereotypically participates in.
frameExamples: The massive metal foot <t>hit</t> the ground with a huge thud.
Her shouts <t>echoed</t> around the cylinder formed by the walls.
Venus <t>rose</t> at 5:23 AM, twenty minutes before the sun which reached the horizon at 5:43 AM.
I awoke to the <t>clash</t> of a jackhammer on concrete.
He <t>slammed</t> his fist down on the table and bellowed something unintelligible.
He put two <t>splashes</t> of cologne on his face.

The Path of the Sound's movement is any description of its trajectory of motion which is neither a Location_of_sound_source or a Goal.
The point-like entity which produces the <fen>Sound</fen>.
A description of the location where the <fen>Sound</fen> ends up.
The time when  the <fen>Sound</fen> movement occurs.
A setting in which <fen>Sound</fen> movement happens.
An entity which is periodically visible from the earth's surface.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Astronomical_entity</fen> appears.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> from which the motion of the <fen>Astronomical_entity</fen> is viewed.
An entity that is construed as a single point source emitting sound.

The location at which sound is produced. This role differs from Location_of_sound_source in that it does not highlight the sound's spreading from its source to the perceiver's location, which is usually indicated by the preposition 'from'.
The <fen>Impactee</fen> is the entity which is hit by the <fen>Impactor</fen>.
The <fen>Impactor</fen> is the entity that hits the <fen>Impactee</fen> because of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s efforts.
The <fen>Impactors</fen> are the multiple entities that collide.
The <fen>Agent</fen>  causes an impact.

The <fen>Cause</fen> marks expressions that indicate some non-intentional, 
typically non-human, force that causes an <fen>Impactor</fen> to make sudden, 
forcible contact with an Impactee.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen>  when the impact occurs.
Where the event takes place.
An abstract or concrete undelimited entity that is measured by the <fen>Event</fen>.
The event that a delimitable quantity or duration of an <fen>Entity</fen> participates in.
